The paper deals with secure transmission of information over a wiretap channel with side information available at the receiver. This involves coding theory, information theory, and signal processing, which are all covered under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also deals with security and privacy, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of hybrid digital-analog coding schemes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The presence of side information at the receiver suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
